Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel and grate the @ginger{1}(peeled and grated). Halve the @lime{1}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Drain and rinse the @lentils{1%pack} in a #sieve{}.

Cut the @broccoli{1}(cut into florets) into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets. Cut the lime into quarters.

Pop the broccoli onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until the edges are crispy and slightly charred, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Place a large #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle}.

Fry the @onion{}, @garlic{} and @ginger{} for ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the @lentils{}, @vegetable stock{1%sachet} and @coconut milk{2%packs} to the pot.

Cover and simmer for ~{15-20%minutes}, stirring frequently. Add a little @water{1%little} if the lentils stick.

When your stew is almost cooked, lightly moisten the @naan{2} breads with a little @water{1%little}.

Bake them for ~{3-5%minutes} to warm them up.

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

When the stew is cooked, add the broccoli and @baby spinach{60%g} to the pot (reserve just a few leaves for serving).

Stir in the juice of half the lime wedges.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Mix well and cook for ~{2%minutes}.

Divide the stewed lentils between #bowls{}.

Serve any remaining lime wedges alongside.

Garnish with coriander.

Serve with the warm naan.